  "100/300 means $100,000 max per person and $300,000 max per accident. Person 1 gets $100,000 (capped), Person 2 gets $80,000, Person 3 gets $50,000. Total = $230,000, which is under the $300,000 per-accident limit.": "",
  "A family pays $600/month for health insurance with a $2,000 deductible, and they typically spend $5,000/year in medical costs. If they switch to a $400/month plan with a $5,000 deductible and no expected medical events, which plan is cheaper for the year?": "",
