  "The $400/month plan at $9,800 total": "",
  "With no medical events, the $400/month plan costs only $4,800 in premiums. The $600/month plan costs $7,200 in premiums alone. High-deductible plans save money when you rarely use medical services.": "",
  "Derek earns $70,000/year and becomes disabled. His employer-provided disability insurance replaces 60% of income with a 90-day waiting period. How much will he receive monthly once benefits start?": "",
  "$4,200": "",
  "$2,917": "",
