  "A couple is comparing two health plans for their family of four. Plan X: $800/month premium, $1,000 deductible, 80/20 coinsurance, $8,000 out-of-pocket max. Plan Y: $500/month premium, $4,000 deductible, 70/30 coinsurance, $12,000 out-of-pocket max. They expect $15,000 in medical costs this year. Which plan costs less total?": "",
